sources.title: The Manster (1959 Sci-Fi) Half-Man, Half-Monster!
sources.description:
The Manster (双頭の殺人鬼 / The Two Headed Monster) is a 1959 American science-fiction horror film. Shot in Japan, it was directed by George P. Breakston and Kenneth G. Crane from a screenplay by Walter J. Sheldon. 

Synopsis:
A deadly experiment gone wrong, creating a two-headed nightmare!
After a scientist's experiment goes wrong, an American reporter slowly turns into a hideous creature with two heads. With his monstrous side taking over, he becomes a threat to everyone around him.

Main Actors: 
Peter Dyneley - Larry Stanford
Jane Hylton - Linda Stanford
Tetsu Nakamura - Dr. Robert Suzuki
Terri Zimmern - Tara
Jerry Ito - Police Supt. Aida

Black & White version: https://youtu.be/unyV97WKNzY


00:00 Full movie (with subtitles)
05:16 Dr. Suzuki begins his sinister experiments, targeting journalist Larry Stanford as his next subject.
14:40 Larry starts experiencing strange physical and emotional changes after his visit to Suzuki's lab.
26:00 Larry's wife, Linda, grows concerned as his behavior becomes erratic and unrecognizable.
38:12 A horrifying transformation begins as Larry discovers a second head growing on his shoulder.
56:12 Larry, now half-human and half-monster, goes on a violent rampage through Tokyo.
1:05:00 Linda confronts Larry, pleading for him to fight the monster within and return to her.
1:11:00 The film concludes with a tragic resolution as Larry sacrifices himself to stop the chaos.
